<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENT PAPERBACKS: SPENCE + LILA BY BOBBIE ANN MASON (HARPER &amp; ROW: $6.95, 
ILLUSTRATED) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A ruminative novel about the love and interdependence that bind a taciturn 
farmer and his gregarious wife. When Lila has to undergo surgery for breast 
cancer and arterial blockage, the sophisticated technology of modern medicine 
forces the couple to confront the coldly mechanized world of the '80s, which 
they have managed to keep at arm's length. 
</P>
<P>
Their Kentucky farm has become a retreat to an older time and a mellowed vision 
of agricultural life. But the pain of separation is more wrenching than the 
sense of dislocation. Lila and Spence discover they are lost without each 
other, a fact that their well-meaning children are unable to disguise. Bobbie 
Ann Mason draws a warm portrait of two people joined by an enduring affection, 
tempered by years of conjugal life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
