<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCAVENGER HUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Linda Deutsch's article about the HumanRace, the around-the-world travel 
adventure contest ("Around the World in a Daze," Jan. 21), was entertaining but 
unfortunately not very accurate. From the beginning, Linda failed to appreciate 
that she had entered a challenging competitive race, not a relaxed tour where 
she could socialize with her correspondent friends. 
</P>
<P>
Realizing after the first day that she didn't have a chance of winning, Linda 
became so caught up in her own anger she failed to see and realize that most of 
the other participants were having a fantastic once-in-a-lifetime experience. 
To say Linda complained is putting it mildly. In spite of herself, Linda 
portrays the HumanRace as a fascinating challenge for the right person. 
</P>
<P>
JONATHAN H. BASSAN 
</P>
<P>
HUMANRACE INC. 
</P>
<P>
Montecito 
