<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEAN TIMES FOR FOREIGN MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am frustrated by the ever-shrinking availability of foreign-language films in 
Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Imagine how I felt when I experienced the same problem when visiting France a 
year ago. The triplex in Avignon offered a choice of (1) a Rambo movie, (2) 
Mickey Rourke and (3) Schwarzenegger. If you can't find a French film in 
France, where then? 
</P>
<P>
ROXANE ALKASLASSY 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
