<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEAN TIMES FOR FOREIGN MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Since Filmex's demise in 1985, (foreign film) pickings have been mighty slim. 
</P>
<P>
My colleagues and I intend to correct this ridiculous state of affairs with the 
establishment of the American Cinematheque. Until mid-1993, when we're 
scheduled to open the doors of our permanent home, it appears that our weekend 
events and the UCLA Archive programs will make up the mainstream of 
foreign-language film programming. 
</P>
<P>
Later this year we will be presenting 16 films by the great Japanese masters as 
part of the Los Angeles Festival. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, I thank Benson for raising this problem. It is certainly an outrage 
that our nation's second city is so culturally deprived due to lackadaisical 
distributors. 
</P>
<P>
GARY ESSERT 
