<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEAN TIMES FOR FOREIGN MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As the owners of our area's only cinema offering foreign fare for the past 11 
years, the last few years have been discouraging. 
</P>
<P>
One problem arising from the disappearance of small distributors of alternative 
films is the sorry fact of major distributors picking up small films and 
placing them in Screen 10 of a multi-screen theater, overlooking the 
independent cinemas that, often, would be a far better showcase. 
</P>
<P>
Benson is right about the disinterest in subtitled films by today's high school 
and college students -- the same group that spearheaded interest earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Think back to the last great foreign-language film you saw -- maybe the popular 
"My Life as a Dog" -- and we'll guarantee that the last thing you'll remember 
was that it was subtitled. 
</P>
<P>
JIM and PATTY DEE 
</P>
<P>
Owners, Palm Theatre 
</P>
