<HEADLINE>
<P>
KHJ'S NEWSCASTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Henry's description of KCAL's former news operation as "lackluster and 
under-performing" shows a remarkable ignorance of both the Los Angeles market 
and his current ratings (about 25% below a year ago). The pre-Disney news team 
was well-respected locally, bringing in dozens of Emmys and Golden Mike Awards 
over the 15 years of my tenure there. 
</P>
<P>
(Channel 9 won no awards this year.) 
</P>
<P>
"Undercapitalized and over-performing" would have been a more accurate 
description of the KHJ news department. Mr. Henry is from WOTV-TV in Grand 
Rapids, Mich., in the country's No. 37 TV market. He could not possibly know 
the kind of person it takes to dispatch six remote trucks: His former station 
had two microwave trucks. 
</P>
<P>
JODY MILLER 
</P>
<P>
(Former art director, 
</P>
<P>
KHJ-TV, 1983-87) 
</P>
<P>
Encino 
</P>
<P>
 Before working in Grand Rapids, Henry was with a station in Dallas, part of a 
market that is in the Top 10. 
</P>
