<P>
20 DIE IN RETALIATION RAID ON SOUTH PAKISTAN VILLAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KARACHI, Pakistan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bandits killed 20 people in a raid on a village in southern Pakistan, police 
said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The raiders opened fire indiscriminately in Hashimjahbhan on Thursday night, 
apparently in retaliation for the death of their gang leader in a gun battle 
with police two days ago. 
</P>
