<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorist on the San Diego-Coronado Bay Bridge stopped his car in mid-span 
about 5 p.m. Saturday and jumped to his death, San Diego police said. 
</P>
<P>
The man was identified as William K. Klein, 40, of Philadelphia, by San Diego 
County Coroner Chuck Kelly. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego police said that the apparent suicide victim was driving east on the 
bridge when he stopped and jumped over the side. A San Diego Harbor Police 
patrol boat, which was nearby, recovered the body within a few minutes. 
</P>
