<HEADLINE>
<P>
DECISION TO DISARM RATHER THAN SHOOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Ana police officers who responded to the domestic violence dispute 
(Feb. 19) where a man was allegedly threatening family members with a loaded 
handgun are a credit to the Police Department for not using deadly force when 
they were justified in doing so. 
</P>
<P>
Whoever made the decision to disarm the man rather than shoot him has shown a 
fine example of restrained response. 
</P>
<P>
These officers were obviously highly skilled and their decision not to take a 
human life hopefully will encourage other officers in Orange County to follow 
their lead, especially in situations where unarmed suspects are involved. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL MOHON 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
<P>
 Mohon is a prisoner in the Orange County Jail. 
</P>
<P>
