<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAYOR'S NOTE ON PRAYERS INSPIRES VARIED REACTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In my opinion, Mayor Richard B. Edgar of Tustin is to be congratulated on his 
forthright and just proposal concerning invocations at City Council meetings. 
</P>
<P>
Being of no particular religious persuasion, I can understand why others like 
myself or people of any but the Christian faith might feel left out or offended 
with the numerous references to Jesus, etc., which seem to be customary in 
invocations at most public gatherings. 
</P>
<P>
Possibly a moment of silence and contemplation at the start of each meeting 
would serve to create the desired atmosphere of seriousness and solemnity 
without causing resentment on anyone's part. I think Mayor Edgar is to be 
commended for his perception and sensitivity in this matter. 
</P>
<P>
REBECCA F. McLEAN 
</P>
<P>
Brea 
</P>
</TEXT>
