<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG WEST CONFERENCE WOMEN'S TOURNAMENT; 
</P>
<P>
LONG BEACH BREAKS PACIFIC BUBBLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dana Wilkerson drove the length of the court and hit a shot from the lane with 
two seconds left, lifting Cal State Long Beach to an 85-83 victory over Pacific 
Saturday in a semifinal game of the Big West Conference women's basketball 
tournament at Long Beach Arena. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific's Julie Szukalski, a 6-foot-3 senior center, scored a tournament-record 
40 points, but the Tigers' bid for a second consecutive upset fell just short. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific (15-15) beat 12th-ranked Hawaii Thursday, and came back after trailing 
13th-ranked Long Beach by nine at halftime to tie the score with 10 seconds 
left on a layup by Szukalski. 
</P>
<P>
Szukalski made 15 of 22 shots, and 10 of 12 free throws. She also had 18 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Penny Moore scored 24 points for Long Beach. Trise Jackson added 16 and 
Angelique Lee had 15. 
</P>
<P>
The 49ers' victory, the 300th of Coach Joan Bonvicini's career, sends Long 
Beach (24-7) into the tournament final today against top-seeded Nevada Las 
Vegas. ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
