<P>
FINLAND'S LAPPALAINEN SCORES FIRST TRANS-AM VICTORY IN 19 STARTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAV GLICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHOENIX 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Finland's Robert Lappalainen, driving a Jack Roush-prepared Ford Mustang, won a 
caution-flag slowed Sports Car Club of America Trans-Am race Saturday on a 
street course in downtown Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
Roush Mustangs also finished third, driven by Max Jones of Long Beach, and 
fourth, with Lyn St. James of Ft. 
</P>
<P>
Lauderdale, Fla. Second was former Indy car driver Chris Knifel of Lake 
Forrest, Ill., in a Chevrolet Beretta. 
</P>
<P>
It was Lappalainen's first victory in 19 Trans-Am starts. He took the lead from 
St. James on lap 30 of the 49-lap race and held it to the end. 
</P>
<P>
Actor Paul Newman, making a surprise start after telling associates that he had 
retired from racing at age 65, finished eighth in an Oldsmobile Cutlass. SHAV 
GLICK 
