<P>
Pirmin Zurbriggen of Switzerland, retiring after this season, clinched the 
World Cup super giant slalom title by winning the event's season finale at 
Hemsedal, Norway. 
</P>
<P>
Zurbriggen flashed down the Bergaloypa track, shortened by 458 meters to 1,710 
meters because of strong winds at the top of the course, in 1 minute, 5.57 
seconds for his 29th World Cup race victory. 
