<HEADLINE>
<P>
LACKING DIRECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Not only would Steinbeck have trouble writing about Cannery Row ("Even 
Steinbeck Might Have Trouble Writing About Cannery Row Today," Feb. 18). 
</P>
<P>
So did Phyllis J. Hanniver. She should have a better sense of the directions 
and geography of the Monterey area, living as she does in Seaside. The Monterey 
Aquarium is at the north, not south, end of Cannery Row. All the other 
directions are also incorrect. To go east on David Avenue would put one in the 
bay. I suppose, in a relative sense, one travels south along the coast from San 
Francisco, but it would be a surprise to see the sun rise in the west, even in 
a relative sense. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD BRAUN 
</P>
<P>
Simi Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
