<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTORIST KILLED AFTER HITTING STREET LIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Huntington Beach man was killed early Saturday after losing control of his 
car and striking a street light on Coast Highway, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Walter Russell Morris, 33, died of massive head injuries at Western Medical 
Center-Santa Ana after the crash about 12:35 a.m. east of 61st Street, police 
said. The cause of the crash is under investigation. 
</P>
