<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN, 58, DIES AFTER CAR HITS POLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WESTMINSTER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 58-year-old Garden Grove woman died Saturday morning after her car ran into a 
utility pole on Magnolia Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Lois Hardy was driving north on Magnolia Street at 7 a.m. when her car veered 
and struck the right curb, then ran onto the sidewalk and hit a pole near Trini 
Circle, Westminster Police Lt. Andrew Hall said. Police do not know why she 
lost control of the car, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Hardy was treated at the scene by medics and taken to Fountain Valley Regional 
Hospital and Medical Center, where she died of internal injuries, Hall said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
