<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOARA BASEBALL TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
Katella 7, Servite 4 -- The score was tied, 4-4, in the seventh inning when 
Brandon Farley hit a one-out three-run home run to give Katella (4-1) the 
victory at Glover Stadium. All of Katella's runs came on homers: Jeff Evans had 
a two-run shot in the fourth and Eric Boyd a two-run shot in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
In the fifth-place game: 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 9, Fountain Valley 4 -- Matt Svoboda went two for three and had two 
RBIs to lead an 11-hit attack for El Dorado (4-1), which built a 9-1 lead 
through six innings. Andy Brazeel (4-0), the second of four Golden Hawk 
pitchers, threw 2 1/3 innings for the victory. He entered the game with the 
bases loaded and two out in the third inning, striking out the next batter to 
preserve a 3-1 El Dorado lead. 
</P>
<P>
In the seventh-place game: 
</P>
<P>
Diamond Bar 5, Dana Hills 1 -- Kevin Ware was two for three with three RBIs and 
Mark Johnson pitched six innings, gave up two hits and struck out eight for 
Diamond Bar at Boysen Park. 
</P>
<P>
In the consolation championship: 
</P>
<P>
Villa Park 1, Newbury Park 0 -- Matt Quint's sacrifice fly scored Chad Vert in 
the second inning for Villa Park. 
</P>
<P>
In other consolation games: 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 8, Los Alamitos 2 -- Laguna Hills (3-4) was led by Tom Lloyd, who 
had four hits and scored three runs. 
</P>
<P>
Sunny Hills 11, Savanna 2 -- Jason Sugarman had two hits, three runs scored, 
four RBIs and homered in the sixth and Ryan Frace homered with one on in the 
fourth inning. 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 1, Huntington Beach 0 -- A pick-off attempt was thrown away allowing 
La Quinta to score in the fifth inning. La Quinta's John Miali pitched four 
perfect innings and Walter Dawkins (1-0) did not allow a hit in three innings, 
walking one and hitting one batter. 
</P>
<P>
Western 8, Irvine 6 -- Host Western (2-2-1) was led by Robert Legender's two 
doubles and three RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
Marina 12, Anaheim 1 -- Robin Lindsey had three hits, including a three-run 
homer in the second, to lead host Marina (2-2-1). 
</P>
<P>
University 3, Magnolia 1 -- Billy Thompson had two hits and an RBI to lead host 
Magnolia. 
</P>
<P>
Pacifica 8, San Clemente 4 -- Host Pacifica was led by Chris Castellano's two 
hits and three runs. 
</P>
<P>
Santiago 10, Cypress 4 -- Steve Garza tripled with the bases loaded in top of 
seventh inning and had four RBIs to key a seven-run inning which brought 
Santiago (5-2) back from a 4-3 deficit. Adrian Borbon hit a two-run home run in 
the seventh for Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
Riverside North 3, Kennedy 2 -- Randy Hernandez singled home Bill Brooks to 
give North the victory in the bottom of the seventh at Brookhurst Park. 
</P>
