<P>
The importance of writers in the success of a television series was especially 
significant this season. 
</P>
<P>
The highly successful "Roseanne" was a hit because of scripts that would be 
hard for anyone to harm. We also had "Sister Kate," which had all the elements 
for success except the most important one: Stephanie Beacham was superb as the 
nun with the caustic tongue and the children were adorable, but the plots were 
often stupid and contrived. Then you have the best of both worlds -- Candice 
Bergen in "Murphy Brown." 
</P>
<P>
Pat Silver, Van Nuys 
