<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO RE-WATCH; 
</P>
<P>
ED GOES TO BAT FOR THE DODGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So, you think that all Mr. Ed can do is talk? 
</P>
<P>
You must be thinking of some other talking horse. This one has been a 
successful businessman, an artist and a spy. 
</P>
<P>
He can even teach the Los Angeles Dodgers a thing or two, which he does on "Mr. 
Ed" at 11 p.m. Friday on Nickelodeon. 
</P>
<P>
Ed, pretending he's Wilbur, calls Dodgers Coach Leo Durocher with tips to solve 
some of the team's batting problems. When the advice works, Wilbur is invited 
to a practice session to give him more. Ed, being the brains in the Post 
household, comes along to coach Wilbur coach the players. 
</P>
<P>
At Dodger Stadium, Ed shows once again that he's not all talk. By the end of 
practice, you'll be wishing Tommy Lasorda had him around last year. 
</P>
<P>
In another tie-in with a local sports team, Los Angeles Rams lineman Deacon 
Jones helps Peter discover that it's OK for macho men to sing on "The Brady 
Bunch" (1:35 p.m. Tuesday on TBS). 
</P>
</TEXT>
