ALSO WORTH WATCHING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
King Kong's favorite leading lady, Fay Wray, plays an ex-movie star in "Perry 
Mason" (9:05 a.m. Thursday on TBS). 
</P>
<P>
James Woods, now not exactly a stranger to misfit roles, is a freeway sniper on 
"Police Story" (midnight Monday on KCAL), in an episode from the mid-U70s. 
</P>
<P>
Before there was "Magnum, P.I.," there was Lance White for Tom Selleck. In one 
of the best-ever "Rockford Files" (noon Saturday on KCOP), three very different 
private eyes-the very human Jim Rockford, the practically perfect Lance White 
and the nerdy Fred Beamer-try to solve a murder at a private investigators' 
convention. 
</P>
<P>
Surfing footage from the documentary "The Endless Summer" was used in the 
"Batman" episode "Surf's Up! Joker's Under!S (2:30 p.m. Sunday on KTTV), in 
which the archvillain tries to become world surfing champ. 
</P>
<P>
"Mork Returns" to Milwaukee on "Happy Days" (9 a.m. Monday on KTLA), where he 
got his start on Earth. Richie shows him the value of human relationships by 
recalling moments with his family and friends. 
</P>
<P>
Hoss tries to prove that he did indeed see a "little green feller" at the 
Ponderosa on "Hoss and the Leprechauns," a fitting episode of "Bonanza" (noon 
Friday on KTLA) to be aired the day before St. Patrick's Day. 
</P>
<P>
Richie and Fonzie are the reluctant grooms in "Shotgun Wedding," which starts 
on "Happy Days" (9 a.m. Thursday on KTLA) and ends on "Laverne &amp; Shirley" 
immediately afterward. The pair try to get out of having to marry a couple of 
backwoods beauties by claiming that they are already spoken for-by Laverne De 
Fazio and Shirley Feeney. 
</P>
<P>
"Phyllis Whips Inflation" -- and picked up a best-supporting-actress Emmy for 
it-on "The Mary Tyler Moore Show" (9:30 p.m. Friday on KDOC). It was Cloris 
Leachman's last regular appearance on the show (she would go on to her own 
series). The plot has Phyllis forced to find work when Lars takes away her 
credit cards. 
</P>
<P>
In the re-edited pilot of "The Bob Newhart Show" (8 p.m. Saturday on KDOC), 
Emily and Bob want to adopt a child. 
