<HEADLINE>
<P>
KELSEY BREAKS THE "LAW" 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For me, "L.A. Law" is indisputably the high point of the viewing week. 
</P>
<P>
It rivals anything on PBS, which I usually watch. However, two recent programs 
focused on Ann Kelsey. She is a very jealous, hateful and spiteful person. I 
know that such people do exist; in fact, I had such a "boss lady" myself once. 
Some of the other workers referred to her as a "witch on wheels." I realize 
that the series always tries to get in some conflict by showing all kinds of 
people. However, it is just too painful to watch this greedy and spiteful 
character. 
</P>
<P>
Bernadette McCrumb, Lynwood 
